Reading in aqs air monitor data

#imports the data
aqs_sites <- read_csv("data/interim/aqs_sites.csv")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   site_id.x = col_character(),
##   site_id = col_character(),
##   month_year = col_date(format = ""),
##   site_id_month_year = col_character(),
##   monthly_mean_co = col_double(),
##   monthly_mean_ozone = col_double(),
##   monthly_mean_no2 = col_double(),
##   monthly_mean_pm10 = col_double(),
##   monthly_mean_pm2.5 = col_double(),
##   monthly_mean_so2 = col_double(),
##   longitude = col_double(),
##   latitude = col_double(),
##   idw_index = col_logical()
## )
#selects only the columns we need
aqs_sites <- aqs_sites %>%
  dplyr::select(site_id, longitude, latitude)

#converts from tibble to sf object
aqs_site_sf <- aqs_sites %>%
  st_as_sf(coords = c("longitude", "latitude"), crs = 4326)

plotting air monitor locations

#visualize the aqs code
aqs_site_sf %>%
  ggplot() +
  geom_sf() +
  theme_bw()

Re-thinking the east and west 45 degree extent

I need to calculate the magnitude for the east and west extent points that produces the same longitudinal coordinate as the center upwind point

To calculate magnitude, I need to determine the initial and terminal points of each vector (east and west)

calculating slope for the east and west vectors

#west-slope

west_slope = (upwindextent_west45$long - monitor_coord$long)/ (upwindextent_west45$lat - monitor_coord$lat)

east_slope = (upwindextent_east45$long - monitor_coord$long)/ (upwindextent_east45$lat - monitor_coord$lat)

Point slope formula y y1 = m(x x1)

west_extent_line: y - (monitor_coord\(long) = west_slope*(x - monitor_coord\)lat)

east_extent_line: y - (monitor_coord\(long) = east_slope*(x - monitor_coord\)lat)

calculating the terminal point for the east and west vectors

terminal_x_west <- ((upwind$long - monitor_coord$long)/west_slope) + monitor_coord$lat

terminal_x_east <- ((upwind$long - monitor_coord$long)/east_slope) + monitor_coord$lat

using extent vector terminal points to calculate east and west magnitude

west_magnitude <- sqrt((monitor_coord$lat - terminal_x_west)^2 + (monitor_coord$long - upwind$long)^2)

east_magnitude <- sqrt((monitor_coord$lat - terminal_x_east)^2 + (monitor_coord$long - upwind$long)^2)

creating new east and west upwind extensions, using calculated magnitude

upwindextent_west45mag <- matrix(c('60010003','west_extent','1/1/19',NA,NA,
                (monitor_coord$lat + 
                   (west_magnitude * cos(monitor_coord$wind_direction + 45))),
                 (monitor_coord$long + 
                   (west_magnitude*sin(monitor_coord$wind_direction + 45)))),
                ncol=7, byrow=TRUE)

colnames(upwindextent_west45mag) <- c('site_id', 'point', 
                                 'Jan.date', 'wind_direction', 
                                 'wind_speed', 'lat', 'long')

upwindextent_west45mag <- as.tibble(upwindextent_west45mag)

upwindextent_west45mag$wind_direction <- as.numeric(upwindextent_west45mag$wind_direction)

upwindextent_west45mag$wind_speed <- as.numeric(upwindextent_west45mag$wind_speed)

upwindextent_west45mag$lat <- as.numeric(upwindextent_west45mag$lat)

upwindextent_west45mag$long <- as.numeric(upwindextent_west45mag$long)

#east

upwindextent_east45mag <- matrix(c('60010003','east_extent','1/1/19',NA,NA,
                (monitor_coord$lat + 
                   (east_magnitude * cos(monitor_coord$wind_direction - 45))),
                 (monitor_coord$long +
